She turned to Phil McGraw, better known as Dr. Phil, television psychologist to the masses.
"We don't shut the country down for that," said Dr. Phil, after he cited inaccurate statistics on accidental deaths.
"People are dying from the coronavirus," Dr. Phil said.
(Unlike Dr. Phil, both Dr. Oz and Dr. Drew are physicians, though neither is an expert in infectious diseases.)
"If 4% of people who routinely went swimming would die & 15% would end up in the hospital, I guarantee Dr. Phil would not go swimming."